    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="555"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/10–2346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Langdon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-28">October 28,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. Cable from Kim Sung Soo<note n="63" xml:id="d555fn1">Telegram from Seoul,
                        October 21, received October 23, not printed. It was signed as from
                        “Chairman the Democratic Party of Korea”.</note> to ActSec asks for true
                    facts concerning press report that secret agreement made at Potsdam provided <pb
                        facs="0762" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> for partition of Korea. Advise him
                    sole agreement at Potsdam which concerned Korea was provision in published
                    declaration that “the terms of the Cairo declaration shall be carried out.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
